sentences.original:
In acceptance sampling, the probability of acceptance depends on:
 the quality level (percent nonconforming) of the lot under inspection;
 the acceptance criterion (i.e. for the particular sampling plan);
 the variation of the characteristic within the lot; and
 the bias and variation inherent in the measurement process (in the case of non-negligible analytical uncertainty).
In practice, the quality level (percent nonconforming) of a lot is not known beforehand; however, for a particular acceptance sampling plan, it is possible to calculate the probability of acceptance at any quality level.
